---
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Stage from "~/components/Stage.astro";
---

<Section id="delta" num="10" title="Delta synchronization">
  <p>
    A full UTXO snapshot is many gigabytes. Clients can't afford to
    re-download one per block. BitcoinPIR servers publish a
    <strong>snapshot chain</strong>: one large base snapshot at height
    <code>V0</code>, then small <em>deltas</em> stacking on top.
  </p>

  <p>
    The client tracks its own last-known version and asks the server's
    catalog for the shortest chain of deltas that will bring it up to the
    current tip. The SDK resolves this as a BFS on the
    <code>(base_height → tip_height)</code> graph, and caps the chain at
    <code>MAX_DELTA_CHAIN_LENGTH = 5</code> steps — beyond that it's cheaper
    to just fetch a fresh snapshot.
  </p>

  <pre><code>// pir-sdk/src/sync.rs:15
pub const MAX_DELTA_CHAIN_LENGTH: usize = 5;</code></pre>

  <Stage
    caption="A client at V0 walks a BFS-shortest chain of deltas to reach V3. Longer chains fall back to fetching the latest full snapshot."
    label="Delta sync chain"
  >
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 220" role="img"
      aria-label="A snapshot V0 plus three small deltas merge into the current version V3."
      data-anim="delta">
      <defs>
        <marker id="arrD" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5"
          markerWidth="5" markerHeight="5" orient="auto">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--accent)"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
      <!-- V0 -->
      <g transform="translate(20,50)">
        <rect width="100" height="90" rx="8" class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="50" y="22" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="var(--fg)"
          font-weight="600">V0</text>
        <text x="50" y="38" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">full snapshot</text>
        <rect x="16" y="50" width="68" height="28" rx="3" fill="var(--fg-muted)"
          opacity="0.35"/>
        <text x="50" y="67" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="var(--fg)">
          ~2 GB
        </text>
      </g>
      <!-- V0 → V1 -->
      <g class="d d1" transform="translate(150,70)">
        <rect width="64" height="50" rx="6" fill="var(--accent-bg)"
          stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.3"/>
        <text x="32" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="var(--accent)"
          font-weight="600">Δ₁</text>
        <text x="32" y="37" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" class="svg-label">
          ~15 MB
        </text>
        <path d="M -30 25 L -2 25" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.5"
          marker-end="url(#arrD)" fill="none"/>
      </g>
      <!-- V1 → V2 -->
      <g class="d d2" transform="translate(248,70)">
        <rect width="64" height="50" rx="6" fill="var(--accent-bg)"
          stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.3"/>
        <text x="32" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="var(--accent)"
          font-weight="600">Δ₂</text>
        <text x="32" y="37" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" class="svg-label">
          ~18 MB
        </text>
        <path d="M -30 25 L -2 25" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.5"
          marker-end="url(#arrD)" fill="none"/>
      </g>
      <!-- V2 → V3 -->
      <g class="d d3" transform="translate(346,70)">
        <rect width="64" height="50" rx="6" fill="var(--accent-bg)"
          stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.3"/>
        <text x="32" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="var(--accent)"
          font-weight="600">Δ₃</text>
        <text x="32" y="37" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" class="svg-label">
          ~22 MB
        </text>
        <path d="M -30 25 L -2 25" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.5"
          marker-end="url(#arrD)" fill="none"/>
      </g>
      <!-- merge arrow -->
      <path d="M 416 95 C 450 95, 470 95, 500 95"
        stroke="var(--ok)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"
        marker-end="url(#arrD)"/>
      <!-- V3 -->
      <g transform="translate(500,50)" class="v3">
        <rect width="100" height="90" rx="8" fill="var(--accent-bg)"
          stroke="var(--ok)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="50" y="22" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="var(--ok)"
          font-weight="600">V3</text>
        <text x="50" y="38" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">current tip</text>
        <rect x="16" y="50" width="68" height="28" rx="3" fill="var(--ok)"
          opacity="0.35"/>
        <text x="50" y="67" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="var(--fg)">
          merged view
        </text>
      </g>

      <text x="340" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">
        each Δ is itself PIR-queried and Merkle-verified — never downloaded whole
      </text>
    </svg>
  </Stage>

  <p>
    An important subtlety: the deltas aren't applied as plain data
    overlays. Each delta is its own PIR-queryable cuckoo dataset with its
    own Merkle root. The client issues the same padded, Merkle-verified
    query path against each one, then merges the results. If no delta
    contains a hit, the client also needs Merkle-verified absence proofs
    from <em>every</em> delta — otherwise a missing delta could hide a
    recent spend.
  </p>
</Section>

<style>
  [data-anim="delta"] .d, [data-anim="delta"] .v3 { opacity: 0; }
  [data-anim="delta"].play .d1 { animation: pop 0.5s var(--ease) 0.4s forwards; }
  [data-anim="delta"].play .d2 { animation: pop 0.5s var(--ease) 0.9s forwards; }
  [data-anim="delta"].play .d3 { animation: pop 0.5s var(--ease) 1.4s forwards; }
  [data-anim="delta"].play .v3 { animation: pop 0.6s var(--ease) 2.0s forwards; }
  @keyframes pop {
    0%   { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); }
    100% { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    [data-anim="delta"] .d, [data-anim="delta"] .v3 { opacity: 1 !important; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-anim="delta"]').forEach((svg) => {
    const stage = svg.closest("[data-stage]");
    const run = () => {
      svg.classList.remove("play");
      void svg.getBoundingClientRect();
      svg.classList.add("play");
    };
    stage?.addEventListener("stage:visible", run);
    svg.addEventListener("click", run);
  });
</script>
